title: The second part of the notorious impostor compleating the history of the life, cheats, &c. of William Morrell, alias Bowyer, sometime of Banbury, chirurgeon. Who lately personated Humphrey Wickham of Swackly, in the county of Oxon, Esquire, at a bakers house in the Strand, where he died the third of Jan. 1691/2. Together with some further passages relating to his sickness and death not before mentioned.
author: Settle, Elkanah, 1648-1724.
publicationStmtPublisher: printed for Abel Roper at the Mytre near Temple-Bar,
